# <%= className %>

Compliance event logger service (AFASA pattern). Generated by `jsbb` v0.1.

## Stack

- **Spring Boot** <%= springBootVersion %>
- **Java** <%= javaVersion %> with virtual threads (`spring.threads.virtual.enabled=true`)
- **Database** Azure SQL (with Flyway migrations)
- **Distributed scheduling** Spring `@Scheduled` + ShedLock
- **Resilience** Resilience4j (retry, circuit-breaker, time-limiter)
- **Observability** Micrometer + Prometheus, Spring Boot Actuator
- **API documentation** SpringDoc OpenAPI / Swagger UI

## Quick start (local)

```bash
# 1. Start a local SQL Server (Docker)
docker run -d --name <%= projectName %>-sql \
  -e "ACCEPT_EULA=Y" -e "MSSQL_SA_PASSWORD=AfasaTest2026!" \
  -e "MSSQL_PID=Developer" -p 1433:1433 \
  mcr.microsoft.com/mssql/server:2022-latest

# 2. Create AFASA database
docker exec <%= projectName %>-sql /opt/mssql-tools18/bin/sqlcmd \
  -S localhost -U sa -P "AfasaTest2026!" -C -Q "CREATE DATABASE AFASA;"

# 3. Run the application
./mvnw spring-boot:run -Dspring-boot.run.profiles=local
```

Flyway will apply all migrations (V1, V2, R__triggers, R__procedures) on startup.

